      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DESERT LIFE (4) was very good first-up behind a smart type before being outclassed in the Magic Millions 3YO most recently. Right back in grade here and she is open to plenty of improvement back to this grade. May get back in the run, but she can make a statement third-up. BLUE CAN TALK (3) missed last time out when setting the tempo, tiring late when 5.6L off the winner. This is much easier than what she's been racing in her past couple and the inside draw is a big tick. Back to 1000m isn't an issue and she creates plenty of interest. ETERNAL WINE (8) gets the blinkers on first time today third-up into the campaign. She draws a better gate this time around which should see her settle closer in the run. Can bounce back in a big way. SO IMMACULATE (7) is racing in good style recently and can make an impression despite the tricky barrier. HEZANGELIC (1) will be hard to run down from up front.",
